  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n  \r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">ELECTROSTATIC&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Charges can be produced by friction, contact and by electrostatic induction.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Electrostatic induction is the act of charging a neutral body by bringing a charged body close to it without making any contact between the two.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">An electrophorus is used to store charges.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">If an unknown charge is brought near to a charged electroscope, and the leaf diverges more, the known charge is similar to the charge on the electroscope. But if it closes up then it is opposite charge.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The instrument used for securing a large number of similar charges by induction is called<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. capacitor B. electrophorus, C. electroscope D. proof-plane<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">If negative charges are induced on an, electroscope and a positively charged rod is brought near the cap of the electroscope, the leaves will<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. close up, B. become positively charged, C. become negatively charged, D. open further.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:10pt; line-height:115%; font-size:11pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">. Since they are opposite it will close up.<\/span><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "ELECTROSTATIC "
}